      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand that it feels like you're at the end of your rope, and it's incredibly tough when it seems like there's no way out. But remember, even when things seem irreparable, there are always small steps that can lead to improvement. It's not about finding a \"better\" in the traditional sense, but rather finding a way to cope and live with the cracks. Sometimes, reaching out for support can make a big difference, even if it's just one conversation at a time. You don't have to face this alone, and it's okay to acknowledge that you're struggling.",
